Grundmann (eds.), <em>Evangelisches Staatslexikon</em>, Stuttgart:
Kreuz Verlag: 636&ndash;643 [= GS 8]; translated as &ldquo;Society,&rdquo;
Fredric R. Jameson (trans.), <em>Salmagundi</em>, 10&ndash;11 (1969):
144&ndash;153.</li>

<li>1966c, &ldquo;Amorbach,&rdquo; <em>S&uuml;ddeutsche</em>
<em>Zeitung</em> 5/6 (1966), expanded in <em>Ohne</em> <em>Leitbild:
Parva Aesthetica</em>, Frankfurt am Main: Suhrkamp, 1968 [= GS 10.1];
translated as &ldquo;Amorbach,&rdquo; in <em>Without Model: Parva
Aesthetica</em>, Wieland Hoban (trans.), London: Seagull Books, 2023:
13&ndash;21.</li>

<li>1967a, &ldquo;R&eacute;sum&eacute; &uuml;ber
Kulturindustrie,&rdquo; in Theodor W. Adorno, <em>Ohne</em>
<em>Leitbild: Parva Aesthetica</em>, Frankfurt am Main: Suhrkamp:
60&ndash;70 [= GS 10.1]; translated as &ldquo;The Culture Industry
Reconsidered,&rdquo; Anson G. Rabinbach (trans.), in Jay Bernstein
(ed.), <em>The Culture Industry: Selected Essays on Mass Culture</em>,
New York: Routledge, 1991: 98&ndash;106.</li>

<li>1967b, &ldquo;Erziehung nach Auschwitz,&rdquo; in Heinz-Joachim
Heydorn, Berthold Simonsohn, Friedrich Hahn, and Anselmus Hertz
(eds.), <em>Zum</em> <em>Bildungsbegriff der Gegenwart</em>, Frankfurt
am Main: Verlag Moritz Diesterweg: 111&ndash;123 [= GS 10.2]; translated as
&ldquo;Education after Auschwitz,&rdquo; Henry W. Pickford (trans.),
in <em>Critical Models: Interventions and Catchwords</em>, New York:
Columbia University Press, 2005: 191&ndash;204.</li>

<li>1967c [year this transcribed talk was given], <em>Aspekte</em>
<em>des neuen Rechtsradikalismus</em>, in <em>Vortr&auml;ge</em>
<em>1949&ndash;1968</em>, Frankfurt am Main: Suhrkamp, 2019: 440&ndash;467 [= NS
V.1]; translated as <em>Aspects oft he New Right-Wing Extremism</em>,
Wieland Hoban (trans.), Cambridge, Polity: 2020.</li>

<li>1967d, &ldquo;Erziehung &ndash; Wozu? Ein Gespr&auml;ch zwischen
Th. W. Adorno und H. Becker,&rdquo; <em>Neue Sammlung</em> 7 (1967):
1&ndash;10, reprinted in Adorno, <em>Erziehung zur M&uuml;ndigkeit.
Vortr&auml;ge und Gespr&auml;che mit Hellmut Becker 1959&ndash;1969</em>,
Gerd Kadelbach (ed.), Frankfurt am Main: Suhrkamp 1971: 105&ndash;119.</li>

<li>1969a, &ldquo;Sp&auml;tkapitalismus oder
Industriegesellschaft?,&rdquo; Adorno (ed.), <em>Sp&auml;tkapitalismus
oder Industriegesellschaft? Im Auftrag der Deutschen Gesellschaft
f&uuml;r Soziologie</em>, Stuttgart: F. Enke: 12&ndash;26 [= GS 8];
translated as &ldquo;Late Capitalism or Industrial Society?,&rdquo;
Rodney Livingstone (trans.), in Rolf Tiedemann (ed.), <em>Can One Live
after Auschwitz?</em> <em>A Philosophical Reader</em>, Stanford:
Stanford University Press, 2003: 111&ndash;125.</li>

<li>1969b, &ldquo;Zu Subjekt und Objekt,&rdquo; <em>Stichworte</em>,
Frankfurt am Main: Suhrkamp [= GS 10.2]; translated as &ldquo;On
Subject and Object,&rdquo; Henry W. Pickford (trans.), in <em>Critical
Models: Interventions and Catchwords</em>, New York: Columbia
University Press, 2005: 245&ndash;258.</li>

<li>1969c, &ldquo;Marginalien zu Theorie und Praxis,&rdquo; in
<em>Stichworte</em>, Frankfurt am Main: Suhrkamp [= GS 10.2];
translated as &ldquo;Marginalia to Theory and Praxis,&rdquo; Henry W.
Pickford (trans.), in <em>Critical Models: Interventions and
Catchwords</em>, New York: Columbia University Press, 2005:
259&ndash;278.</li>

<li>1969d, &ldquo;Keine Angst vor dem Elfenbeinturm,&rdquo; <em>Der
Spiegel</em> 23/19 (5 May 1969): 204&ndash;209 [= GS 20.1]; translated as
&ldquo;Who&rsquo;s Afraid of the Ivory Tower? A Conversation with
Theodor W. Adorno,&rdquo; Gerhard Richter (trans.),
<em>Monatshefte</em> 94/1 (2002): 10&ndash;23.</li>

<li>1970, <em>&Auml;sthetische</em> <em>Theorie</em>, Frankfurt am
Main: Suhrkamp [= GS 7]; translated as <em>Aesthetic Theory</em>,
Robert Hullot-Kentor (trans.), Minneapolis: University of Minnesota
Press, 1997.</li>

<li>1950, Adorno, Theodor W., Else Frenkel-Brunswik, Daniel Levinson,
and Nevitt Sanford, <em>The Authoritarian Personality</em>, New York:
