<h2 id="Oth">Other Internet Resources</h2>

<ul>

<li><a href="https://www.ub.uni-frankfurt.de/archive/a-z.html" target="other">Archives Center/University Library J.C. Senckenberg</a>
  at the Johann Wolfgang Goethe University in Frankfurt. This university
archive contains the literary bequests of Horkheimer, Pollock, and
other of Adorno&rsquo;s colleagues in the Frankfurt School.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.adornostudies.org/" target="other">Association for Adorno Studies</a></li>

<li><a href="https://www.ifs.uni-frankfurt.de/adorno-archive.html" target="other">Theodor W. Adorno Archive/Institute of Social Research</a>,
  at the Johann Wolfgang Goethe University in Frankfurt.</li>

<li><a href="https://archiv.adk.de/bigobjekt/19345" target="other">Theodor W. Adorno Archive in the Walter Benjamin Archive</a>, 
  at the Akademie der K&uuml;nste in Berlin.</li>

<li><a href="https://adorno-identity.net/documents/" target="other">The Adorno and Identity Seminars: Documents and Video Archive</a>,
  seminars supported by Princeton University, Arizona State
  University, and the University of California, Berkeley.</li>

</ul>

